text: Nicorhynchus (meaning "knucker snout"; a knucker is a type of water dragon) was a pterosaur that has been discovered in both England and Morocco. Both species (N. capito and N. fluviferox) were originally species of Coloborhynchus. ==References== Category:Pterosaurs Category:Cretaceous Category:Animals of Africa
title: Nicorhynchus
